## What Your Employees Will Notice

- **Copilot gets a new AI model option.** Anthropic's Claude Sonnet 5 is now available inside Microsoft 365 Copilot for document, spreadsheet, and presentation work. Employees with Copilot licenses will see this as an additional option. No action required from users; communicate that this is expected behavior.
- **Copilot Cowork is now generally available.** This capability allows Copilot to handle multi-step, cross-application workflows rather than single-question interactions. Employees will see more complex task completion available directly in their familiar Microsoft 365 apps.
- **Outlook will flag replies to outdated email threads.** Coming in August 2026, Outlook for Windows and web will alert users when they are replying to an older message in a thread rather than the most recent one. This small quality-of-life change may prompt brief user questions; it requires no training but a simple heads-up in your next IT newsletter will prevent help desk noise.
- **Planner gets an improved task detail view.** Users will be able to view and edit task details in a side panel without losing their board or grid view. This is a quality-of-life improvement arriving in July 2026.
- **Teams meeting room improvements for Town Hall events.** Organizations running Teams Rooms on Android with a Pro license will gain presenter control over front-of-room displays during Town Hall events, arriving in August 2026.
- **SharePoint AI skills are in broader use.** Microsoft has published detailed guidance on how Copilot in SharePoint is being used internally; if your organization has started SharePoint Copilot deployments, employees may see improved skill recommendations and document-drafting support.

*Sources: [What's New in M365 Copilot — June 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-copilot-blog/what-s-new-in-microsoft-365-copilot-june-2026/ba-p/4529572) · [What's New in Microsoft Teams — June 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-teams-blog/what-s-new-in-microsoft-teams-june-2026-infocomm-edition/ba-p/4531968) · [M365 Roadmap](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap)*

