## What Your Help Desk Should Expect

- **Copilot model selection questions.** With Claude Sonnet 5 added to Microsoft 365 Copilot, users may ask which model to use for which task, or report unexpected behavior if one model responds differently than another. Prepare a brief FAQ for your support team distinguishing the available options.
- **Entra Backup and Recovery inquiries from IT staff.** Identity and security teams may begin asking about how to configure the new backup feature; this is a good signal but requires a coordinated response rather than ad hoc configuration. Escalate to your identity administrator or Microsoft partner.
- **CVE-related patch confirmation requests.** After a large CVE batch, regulated-industry IT teams often receive internal requests from compliance or legal to confirm patch status. Expect your IT team to need time to inventory affected components, particularly if you use AI/ML frameworks, SSH infrastructure, or HTTP/2-exposed services.
- **AI agent behavior questions.** As Copilot Cowork and Sales Agent reach general availability, employees using multi-step AI workflows may report unexpected actions or outputs. Most of these will be user experience questions, but any report of the AI accessing data it should not have accessed should be escalated immediately given the MCP security risks documented this week.
- **Planner and Outlook UI change tickets.** Minor interface changes to Planner task views and the forthcoming Outlook thread-reply notification will generate low volumes of "did something change?" tickets. Brief your help desk in advance.

*Sources: [What's New in M365 Copilot — June 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-copilot-blog/what-s-new-in-microsoft-365-copilot-june-2026/ba-p/4529572) · [Microsoft Security Response Center](https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/) · [Entra Backup and Recovery GA](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/microsoft-entra-backup-and-recovery-is-now-generally-available/ba-p/4521997)*

---

## Cost & Licensing

- **Intune Suite capabilities now included in M365 E3 and E5 (effective July 1, 2026).** Organizations that purchased standalone Intune Suite add-ons should review whether those add-on licenses are now redundant with what is included in their base M365 subscription. This could represent a meaningful cost reduction. Your Microsoft account team or licensing partner can confirm the overlap specific to your agreement.
- **Entra ID P1 or P2 required for Backup and Recovery.** Organizations running on baseline Entra ID (formerly Azure AD Free) will not have access to the new identity backup capability. If your disaster recovery plan requires it, a licensing upgrade may be necessary. This is a budget conversation worth having before an incident, not after.
- **Copilot Cowork and Sales Agent are generally available.** Both are included in Microsoft 365 Copilot licensing. If your organization has Copilot licenses that have not yet been activated or deployed, this week's GA announcements add substantial workflow automation value to licenses you may already be paying for but underutilizing.
- **Claude Sonnet 5 in Copilot carries no additional license cost** for Microsoft 365 Copilot subscribers; it is included as an additional model option at current licensing levels.

*Sources: [Intune Suite in M365 E3/E5](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-intune-blog/advanced-microsoft-intune-capabilities-now-available-in/ba-p/4529335) · [Entra Backup and Recovery GA](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/microsoft-entra-backup-and-recovery-is-now-generally-available/ba-p/4521997) · [Copilot Cowork GA](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-copilot-blog/the-workflow-is-the-product-copilot-cowork-plugins-change-what/ba-p/4531933)*

