## If You Take No Action

**On AI agent security (MCP tool poisoning):** Deployed AI agents that connect to business data and systems through the Model Context Protocol can be manipulated by attackers to read, copy, or transmit sensitive information without user awareness. Microsoft has documented this as an active attack technique, not a theoretical risk. Organizations in regulated industries face direct exposure under HIPAA, SOC 2, and CMMC if sensitive data is exfiltrated through an AI agent and the organization cannot demonstrate it had controls in place. Cyber insurers are beginning to ask about AI governance; an uncontrolled AI agent incident could affect both coverage and premiums.

**On the CVE patch batch:** The vulnerabilities published this week include flaws in core networking and cryptographic protocols. If your environment includes custom applications, AI/ML workloads, or developer tooling built on affected open-source components, and those components are not patched, you carry known, documented, exploitable risk. For organizations under CMMC or HIPAA, failure to patch within a reasonable window after public disclosure is itself a compliance finding, independent of whether exploitation occurs.

**On Entra identity backup:** If your tenant suffers a ransomware attack or a malicious insider deletes or corrupts user accounts, group memberships, Conditional Access policies, or application registrations, and you have not configured Entra Backup and Recovery, restoration requires manual effort that typically takes days and introduces errors. Every day of identity infrastructure downtime directly impairs your employees' ability to work and your organization's ability to operate. The capability is now available; the decision to activate it carries no additional cost for organizations already on Entra P1 or P2.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog — Securing AI Agents](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/06/30/securing-ai-agents-ai-tools-move-from-reading-acting/) · [Microsoft Security Response Center](https://msrc.microsoft.com/update-guide/) · [Entra Backup and Recovery GA](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/microsoft-entra-backup-and-recovery-is-now-generally-available/ba-p/4521997)*